Bye-bye. Love you!

41:40.000 --> 41:42.000
God, she is pretty.

41:42.083 --> 41:45.583
... Spencer.

41:45.666 --> 41:46.958
<i>Magic passes to Kareem.</i>

41:47.041 --> 41:48.583
<i>He's pivoting,</i>
<i>looking for an opening.</i>

41:48.666 --> 41:50.083
<i>Gets some help from</i>
<i>Haywood with a pick.</i>

41:50.166 --> 41:53.041
<i>And he lays it in.</i>
<i>Snug as a bug in a rug.</i>

42:07.791 --> 42:09.750
<i>And the Los Angeles Lakers</i>
<i>now moments away</i>

42:09.833 --> 42:11.625
<i>from avenging their</i>
<i>playoff loss last year</i>

42:11.708 --> 42:12.875
<i>against the SuperSonics.</i>

42:12.958 --> 42:15.083
<i>Boy, the fans here</i>
<i>can taste victory,</i>

42:15.166 --> 42:16.541
<i>and it sure tastes sweet.</i>

42:16.625 --> 42:18.083
Seven! Six!

42:18.166 --> 42:20.041
Five! Four!

42:20.125 --> 42:22.875
Three! Two! One!

42:22.958 --> 42:24.583
- <i> And it's all over,</i>
<i>folks!</i>

42:24.666 --> 42:28.291
<i>Your Los Angeles Lakers</i>
<i>are the new</i>
<i>Western Conference Champs,</i>

42:28.375 --> 42:30.458
<i>behind 38 points by</i>
<i>the captain, Kareem.</i>

43:25.083 --> 43:26.875
<i>Now, all they have</i>
<i>to do is sit back</i>

43:26.958 --> 43:28.125
<i>and wait for a date</i>
<i>with the doctor.</i>

43:28.208 --> 43:30.125
All we care about is that
the boys in Forum Blue

43:30.208 --> 43:31.916
will be there,
and look at 'em celebrating.

43:32.000 --> 43:33.291
Boy, they sure have earned it.

43:33.375 --> 43:35.500
You made me believe, baby.
You made me believe.

43:35.583 --> 43:37.833
<i>And look at Magic out there,</i>
<i>smile shining</i>

43:37.916 --> 43:40.083
<i>like the North Star,</i>
<i>and Dr. Buss,</i>
<i>our other rookie,</i>

43:40.166 --> 43:43.125
<i>must be somewhere</i>
<i>beaming just as bright.</i>

44:05.958 --> 44:09.166
<i>There it is. Philly puts</i>
<i>this one over the top.</i>

44:09.250 --> 44:11.958
<i>And folks dreaming</i>
<i>of a Boston-LA finals</i>

44:12.041 --> 44:14.000
<i>will have to wait another year.</i>

44:14.083 --> 44:16.333
<i>- The 76ers have...</i>
Here we go, fellas.

44:16.416 --> 44:18.125
Philly it is.

44:18.208 --> 44:19.375
Man, I wanted Boston.

44:19.458 --> 44:20.791
Then you a dumbass.

44:20.875 --> 44:22.750
<i>...right here on CBS.</i>

44:26.333 --> 44:27.875
<i>The Celtics have</i>
<i>the best record</i>

44:27.958 --> 44:29.333
<i>of any team</i>
<i>in the league...</i>

44:29.416 --> 44:31.750
Same time next year, asshole.

44:33.000 --> 44:34.125
You know it.

44:34.208 --> 44:35.750
<i>And young Larry Bird may be</i>

44:35.833 --> 44:37.375
<i>disappointed by the outcome,</i>

44:37.458 --> 44:40.791
<i>but after watching his</i>
<i>performance in this series,</i>

44:40.875 --> 44:44.000
<i>he gets my vote</i>
<i>for Rookie of the Year.</i>

44:44.083 --> 44:46.041
<i>Bird led scoring</i>
<i>through the playoffs...</i>

44:46.125 --> 44:48.791
We win it all,
you'll get your due.

44:48.875 --> 44:51.000
<i>...far beyond his age.</i>

44:52.541 --> 44:54.208
Hey, Cap?

44:55.166 --> 44:57.416
We got a situation.

45:03.583 --> 45:05.416
Spence?

45:05.500 --> 45:08.208
- What happened to you?
What's the matter?

45:10.375 --> 45:12.958
I fucked up...

45:13.041 --> 45:16.333
Just... I fucked up, Cap...

45:18.541 --> 45:20.541
I'm sorry...

45:21.750 --> 45:23.333
I fucked up...

45:24.875 --> 45:28.083
Okay. It's okay...

45:28.166 --> 45:31.208
I fucked up...

45:31.291 --> 45:33.916
I'm sorry...
- Aw, fuck.

45:34.000 --> 45:36.375
Goddammit, man.

45:36.458 --> 45:38.125
Man, I can't watch this shit.

45:38.208 --> 45:40.125
There's an institute
in Arizona.

45:40.208 --> 45:43.916
They specialize in something
called aversion therapy.

45:44.000 --> 45:47.583
Spencer would admit
himself after the season.

45:47.666 --> 45:51.083
He's promised me he'll
keep clean through the finals.

45:54.208 --> 45:56.250
If you let him stay.

46:00.958 --> 46:04.416
Look, he's our one true four.

46:04.500 --> 46:05.916
Alright, if we lose him,

46:06.000 --> 46:07.791
that's gonna put a whole
lot on Cap down low.

46:07.875 --> 46:09.250
We gonna need him
in the paint.

46:09.333 --> 46:11.250
Them Twin Towers they got,
Dawkins, Jones.

46:11.333 --> 46:13.791
- Leave them to Chones.
The brother has a problem.

46:13.875 --> 46:15.708
Can't just throw
him to the wolves.

46:15.791 --> 46:17.458
Maybe somebody can just
keep an eye on him.

46:17.541 --> 46:20.416
This is the pros,
not daycare.

46:20.500 --> 46:22.458
Look, Wood's only problem

46:22.541 --> 46:24.375
is that he's a selfish
motherfucker.

46:24.458 --> 46:28.500
All that African brother
Hotep bullshit?

46:28.583 --> 46:31.833
Look, bottom line,
dude's not strong.
He's weak.

46:31.916 --> 46:33.791
And if we let this
motherfucker stay on the team,

46:33.875 --> 46:36.166
then the rest of us
is weak, too.

46:42.166 --> 46:43.750
And you, Buck?

46:48.458 --> 46:50.083
I wanna win a ring.

46:51.250 --> 46:53.208
That's what matters to me.

46:53.291 --> 46:55.708
And I feel bad for dude

46:55.791 --> 46:59.291
if he ain't ready
for what's coming.

46:59.375 --> 47:03.041
But, great man told me winning
in this league takes being hard.

47:08.666 --> 47:09.833
Listen.

47:09.916 --> 47:11.666
He's your teammate.

47:12.583 --> 47:13.916
So, this is a team call.

47:14.000 --> 47:16.333
Let's put it to a vote.

47:24.166 --> 47:25.958
All for cutting Spencer.

47:31.750 --> 47:33.083
Mm-hmm.

47:43.166 --> 47:44.583
All opposed.

48:02.791 --> 48:04.625
White folk still white folking?

48:06.875 --> 48:09.083
I just left.

48:09.166 --> 48:10.291
Hm...

48:29.500 --> 48:31.291
You ever been to Mississippi?

48:32.166 --> 48:33.958
- Never.
- No?

48:34.041 --> 48:35.416
I came up there.

48:35.500 --> 48:37.541
Family of field hands.

48:37.625 --> 48:38.958
<i>They call it sharecropping,</i>

48:39.041 --> 48:40.916
but if there's a difference
between it and slavery,

48:41.000 --> 48:41.875
I ain't see it.

48:41.958 --> 48:44.250
I was born in a barn,

48:44.333 --> 48:46.166
on the same dirt...

48:47.166 --> 48:50.000
as the pigs and chickens.

48:50.083 --> 48:53.416
The only thing that separated
us from them was...

48:55.541 --> 48:57.875
these right here.

48:59.000 --> 49:01.166
<i>Extra bone in each finger.</i>

49:01.250 --> 49:02.583
My Auntie Harriet

49:02.666 --> 49:05.166
<i>seen 'em and went, "Wow."</i>
<i>Touching them, said, uh,</i>

49:05.250 --> 49:08.500
"That boy is blessed.
That boy gonna do some...

49:08.583 --> 49:11.291
That boy gonna do
some great things."

49:12.750 --> 49:14.833
But, along come...

49:14.916 --> 49:18.333
old man Quinn. Field boss.

49:18.416 --> 49:21.500
<i>High yellow nigga.</i>

49:21.583 --> 49:23.375
Quick sight, you'd
think he a-a cracker.

49:23.458 --> 49:25.875
But, he worse than one of 'em.

49:25.958 --> 49:29.291
Used to whistle with
his pinkies in his mouth.

49:30.625 --> 49:33.708
And just like that,
our backs was bent.

49:33.791 --> 49:36.166
Shit, I think
the first real sound

49:36.250 --> 49:38.416
I ever heard was a whistle.

49:40.625 --> 49:42.458
So, he seen my mama
and my auntie

49:42.541 --> 49:44.500
fussing over this
little newborn child

49:44.583 --> 49:48.208
with these fancy little
hands, and took to him.

49:49.583 --> 49:51.208
He knew better.

49:53.916 --> 49:57.333
"Hoo, that boy got
some long fingers!

49:58.083 --> 50:00.083
"Oo-hoo-hoo-wee!

50:00.166 --> 50:03.333
"He gonna make a special...

50:04.166 --> 50:06.000
cotton picker."

50:08.875 --> 50:09.791
Hm.

50:09.875 --> 50:12.625
My mama used to
tell us that story.

50:12.708 --> 50:16.416
Without-- Without
skipping a breath, say,

50:16.500 --> 50:18.500
"God love us."

50:22.125 --> 50:24.541
Now, it took me...

50:24.625 --> 50:26.583
some years

50:26.666 --> 50:29.166
to muster up
the gumption to ask...

50:31.166 --> 50:33.375
"Why...

50:33.458 --> 50:36.500
"are we on the bottom then?

50:36.583 --> 50:40.375
"Everywhere you see
a brown face,

50:40.458 --> 50:42.583
"you see tears on it.

50:44.083 --> 50:48.083
If He love us so damn much,
then why?"

50:51.791 --> 50:53.958
And you know what she said?

50:56.125 --> 50:58.958
"God loves them more."

51:05.500 --> 51:08.208
Yeah, I don't know if
it's-- if there's a God,

51:08.291 --> 51:12.625
I don't know.
But I do know there's a them.

51:12.708 --> 51:17.041
Same ones in that room
right now, deciding my fate!

51:22.791 --> 51:25.291
So, I guess I'll just
wait for the whistle.

51:38.291 --> 51:40.583
This time,
they left it up to us.

51:45.583 --> 51:47.958
The team already voted on it.

51:53.166 --> 51:54.750
Damn!

51:56.458 --> 51:59.583
Damn! Damn it. Damn!

52:09.791 --> 52:11.500
You did your best.

52:13.500 --> 52:15.625
I appreciate it, Cap.

52:23.375 --> 52:25.500
I was the deciding vote.

53:11.166 --> 53:12.250
There we go.

53:22.125 --> 53:23.583
- There we go.

53:26.791 --> 53:27.875
There we go.

53:31.500 --> 53:34.541
- Is that
what I think it is?

53:34.625 --> 53:38.000
Oh hey, Cap.
Been practicing your skyhook.

53:38.083 --> 53:40.541
Way I figure, be seeing
more time in the post

53:40.625 --> 53:43.625
against Philly,
so better have a go-to.

53:48.000 --> 53:51.916
That is not a skyhook.
- Ain't that bad.

53:53.291 --> 53:55.958
Well, why ain't
you show me then?

53:56.041 --> 53:59.333
- Skyhook isn't just
any other shot.

54:00.375 --> 54:01.708
To master it,

54:01.791 --> 54:03.500
a player needs to comprehend

54:03.583 --> 54:04.916
a very important principle.

54:05.000 --> 54:06.375
And what principle is that?

54:06.458 --> 54:09.583
Isolation. Come over here
and play a little defense.

54:09.666 --> 54:12.208
See, when you're the big man,

54:12.291 --> 54:15.000
everybody wants a piece of you.

54:15.083 --> 54:17.666
The skyhook shuts them out.

54:17.750 --> 54:19.166
It turns your body into a wall,

54:19.250 --> 54:22.250
beyond which they can't reach
or even see your face,

54:22.333 --> 54:26.000
which means
they can't predict you.

54:26.083 --> 54:29.333
So, on your own time,
when you're good and ready,

54:29.416 --> 54:31.541
you can leave
their world behind.

54:33.083 --> 54:35.333
You leave the world?

54:35.416 --> 54:37.000
You elevate above it.

54:39.500 --> 54:42.125
Until you're completely
and totally...

54:44.541 --> 54:46.916
- ...alone.

54:47.000 --> 54:50.166
<i>And all they get</i>
<i>to do is watch.</i>

54:50.250 --> 54:52.125
Damn, Cap.

54:52.208 --> 54:55.000
You some kind of poet
or somethin'.

54:55.083 --> 54:56.541
That shit deep.

54:56.625 --> 54:57.875
Alright, let's work on it.

54:57.958 --> 54:59.958
I can't have you fucking up
my shot on the world stage.

55:00.041 --> 55:02.583
Come on, get that
arm up straight,

55:02.666 --> 55:03.875
like the Statue of Liberty.

55:03.958 --> 55:05.458
It's the most elegant finish

55:05.541 --> 55:08.250
in all of sports.

55:08.333 --> 55:10.208
Right on.

55:12.625 --> 55:14.666
- Hey! Sprinkles!

55:15.625 --> 55:16.541
Hey!

55:16.625 --> 55:18.791
- Yeah, that's right.

55:19.750 --> 55:21.500
Wood, Wood, Wood.

55:21.583 --> 55:23.000
What the fuck, brother?

55:23.083 --> 55:26.208
Congrats on the Finals, man.
Time to get that shiny ring, eh?

55:26.291 --> 55:28.708
You still got that magnum?

55:28.791 --> 55:29.958
Oh, man, I got...

55:30.041 --> 55:32.875
I got lots of guns.
I got a bazooka.

55:32.958 --> 55:35.000
I don't care what you use,

55:35.083 --> 55:38.000
as long as it works.

55:38.083 --> 55:41.500
Sure, man. Yeah, right on.
Love to do that for a friend.

55:41.583 --> 55:43.375
You just say the word.

55:43.458 --> 55:45.250
Who do you want me to kill?

55:47.291 --> 55:48.791
The Lakers.
